message: Hey future player! Here's what I learned: Always start by using the 'stove' tool on all 'raw' protein and vegetable ingredients. This usually turns them into valuable 'cooked' items (20 points each). Then, try combining a 'cooked protein' with a 'cooked vegetable' to get a 60-point item. If you have another 'cooked vegetable', combine it with your 60-point item to often reach 80 points! Be careful with 'grain' items, as adding them to complex cooked dishes (especially after reaching 80) often results in 'overcomplicated' items with 0 value, or even negative values if you use 'water'. It's often safest to submit when you have an 80-point item and only grains or the 'water' tool left. The 'water' tool generally reduces value or makes things complicated; I would avoid it entirely unless you have nothing to lose. Good luck!
